{
  "texts": [
    "The same was reported for near-misses not resulting in harm.",
    "8, 10 Similarly, surgical trainees reporting burnout were more likely to shout at their patients and make medical errors.",
    "[11] [12] [13] Factors such as age, marital status, children, work-life balance and mental health are known to contribute to burnout.",
    "14, 15 In particular, female and junior surgical trainees have a higher risk of burnout.",
    "15 However, previous reviews have not focused solely on surgical trainees, particularly those at a junior level and female."
  ]
}